WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:04.930
♪♪

00:06.564 --> 00:07.572
[ANNOYED] Honey?

00:07.596 --> 00:09.455
Do I hear the sound of chicken bones

00:09.480 --> 00:10.943
approaching the disposal?

00:10.945 --> 00:15.056
No, you hear the sound of
chicken bones being disposed of.

00:15.435 --> 00:17.371
[SWITCH CLICKS, DISPOSAL GRINDING]

00:17.396 --> 00:20.152
Oh?! You suddenly want
to help me clean up?!

00:20.154 --> 00:21.498
[GRUNTS]

00:22.489 --> 00:24.222
You can't just throw everything in there

00:24.224 --> 00:25.555
and expect it to disappear.

00:25.580 --> 00:27.233
It's not the ocean, Francine.

00:27.258 --> 00:28.908
B-b-b-burned.

00:28.933 --> 00:30.687
Shut up, Klaus. That wasn't even a burn.

00:30.712 --> 00:33.698
Yeah, Klaus. When I'm burned,
I'll let ya know.

00:33.723 --> 00:38.847
Okay, so no chicken down
the disposal, but...

00:38.872 --> 00:41.082
How about... this?

00:41.107 --> 00:43.116
[CHUCKLING] That... That's funny.

00:43.736 --> 00:45.021
That's making me laugh.

00:45.046 --> 00:47.143
And I've decided to join in the joke!

00:48.534 --> 00:50.352
- [FRIGHTENED GROANS]
- Francine?

00:50.377 --> 00:51.481
Hit the switch.

00:51.506 --> 00:53.496
- [DISPOSAL WHIRRING]
- Okay, we've all had our fun.

00:53.520 --> 00:55.053
Now put me down!

00:55.055 --> 00:56.556
If you insist...

00:56.581 --> 00:59.234
Stan, now you're making me laugh.

00:59.259 --> 01:01.268
And making me kind of hot.

01:01.293 --> 01:02.571
[SHOUTS]

01:02.596 --> 01:04.825
[SCREAMING] Oh, no! Oohheeeghhagh! Help!

01:04.851 --> 01:06.820
[MOCKINGLY] Oohheeeghhagh!

01:06.845 --> 01:07.845
That's you!

01:07.870 --> 01:11.118
I guess you can put
chicken down the drain.

01:11.143 --> 01:12.937
- [LAUGHING DERISIVELY]
- [SCREAMS]

01:12.962 --> 01:14.988
It sounds like everyone's
having a good time.

01:15.013 --> 01:17.134
Yeah, Klaus is in the disposal!

01:17.159 --> 01:18.765
Tell that idiot pieces of shit

01:18.790 --> 01:20.456
are supposed to go in the toilet.

01:20.481 --> 01:24.349
[LAUGHING]

01:24.351 --> 01:26.663
To the ice cream store! My treat!

01:28.732 --> 01:31.166
Remember, I'm a rum raising guy.

01:31.191 --> 01:33.003
Cool, I'll put some in a waffle cone

01:33.028 --> 01:34.229
and throw it in the trash.

01:34.254 --> 01:35.403
[LAUGHTER]

01:35.428 --> 01:37.890
FRANCINE: Now that was a burn, fish.

01:38.298 --> 01:41.042
♪♪

01:41.067 --> 01:44.053
♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

01:44.078 --> 01:47.597
♪ I got a feelin' that
it's gonna be a wonderful day ♪

01:47.622 --> 01:50.569
♪ The sun in the sky has
a smile on his face ♪

01:50.594 --> 01:54.375
♪ And he's shinin'
a salute to the American race ♪

01:57.028 --> 02:00.252
♪ Oh, boy, it's swell to say ♪

02:00.277 --> 02:02.721
♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

02:02.723 --> 02:03.723
Aah!

02:05.236 --> 02:08.190
♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

02:08.215 --> 02:12.733
♪♪

02:12.758 --> 02:15.177
Welp, that was the last straw.

02:15.202 --> 02:16.494
I am leaving.

02:17.105 --> 02:19.106
It's too late for apologies.

02:19.448 --> 02:21.100
Nothing could make it right.

02:21.505 --> 02:24.142
Not even acknowledging
my existence in any way.

02:24.589 --> 02:26.545
Alright, Klaus. What's all this?

02:26.547 --> 02:27.837
You... You're selling lemonade?

02:27.862 --> 02:29.387
No, I'm leaving.

02:29.412 --> 02:31.620
I've never asked for anything
but a little respect.

02:31.645 --> 02:33.987
And it's clear I'm not going to get it.

02:34.012 --> 02:36.338
Okay, okay. I'll buy a lemonade.

02:36.363 --> 02:38.865
[SCREAMS] I'm not selling lemonade!

02:38.890 --> 02:40.613
I'm leaving! Forever!

02:40.638 --> 02:43.562
One day you'll all regret
how you treated me!

02:45.809 --> 02:46.809
Should we stop him?

02:46.834 --> 02:47.943
The lemonade guy?

02:47.968 --> 02:50.116
He's just being dramatic. He'll be back.

02:50.320 --> 02:52.287
_

02:53.751 --> 02:56.886
Okay, kids. Help Mom with the groceries.

02:57.236 --> 02:59.190
Jeff Junior, you stop drawing

02:59.215 --> 03:01.513
rockets shooting lasers on my windows.

03:02.113 --> 03:03.315
[PHONE BEEPS]

03:03.662 --> 03:04.918
Klaus died?

03:05.188 --> 03:06.869
Klaus the fish?

03:06.894 --> 03:09.922
Geez, I haven't seen him
since he walked out.

03:09.924 --> 03:12.966
[MARVIN GAYE'S "I HEARD IT
THROUGH THE GRAPEVINE" PLAYS]

03:12.991 --> 03:15.130
♪♪

03:15.155 --> 03:16.994
_

03:17.019 --> 03:20.857
♪ Ooh, I bet you're
wonderin' how I knew ♪

03:21.793 --> 03:25.670
♪ 'Bout your plans to make me blue ♪

03:25.672 --> 03:29.253
♪ With some other guy you knew before ♪

03:29.278 --> 03:31.421
- ♪ Between the two of us guys ♪
- [PHONE RINGS]

03:31.446 --> 03:33.678
♪ You know I loved you more ♪

03:33.680 --> 03:37.660
♪ It took me by surprise I must say ♪

03:38.171 --> 03:41.680
♪ When I found out yesterday ♪

03:41.705 --> 03:44.810
♪ Don't you know that I heard
it through the grapevine ♪

03:44.835 --> 03:45.962
[PHONE RINGS]

03:46.430 --> 03:47.915
Go for the Stanimal.

03:48.479 --> 03:49.940
Oh, when?

03:50.067 --> 03:51.871
Yeah, I know where Francine's house is.

03:51.896 --> 03:53.682
That's where I used to sleep in my car

03:53.707 --> 03:55.834
until a judge and I came
to a mutual agreement

03:55.836 --> 03:57.702
that Francine be rewarded that car

03:57.704 --> 04:00.005
and I remain 80 yards away at all times.

04:02.709 --> 04:03.709
Hey!

04:03.887 --> 04:04.906
You know the deal.

04:04.931 --> 04:06.130
Neither of us gets to do it

04:06.155 --> 04:08.038
until I can afford a second bullet.

04:09.328 --> 04:12.832
- ♪♪
- _

04:12.857 --> 04:14.992
[DOORBELL RINGS]

04:15.017 --> 04:17.921
[WHIRRING]

04:17.946 --> 04:20.449
Steve. It's been years.

04:20.474 --> 04:21.740
Hello, Mother.

04:24.447 --> 04:27.598
I follow your company on Newstagram.

04:27.623 --> 04:29.945
You just bought freakin' Hawaii!

04:29.970 --> 04:31.796
As a place to store my shoes.

04:31.821 --> 04:33.534
I'm doing quite well, yes.

04:33.559 --> 04:34.973
Is he here?

04:34.975 --> 04:36.775
Of course he's here.

04:36.777 --> 04:38.577
He's my husband now.

04:38.579 --> 04:39.845
And he's your father.

04:39.847 --> 04:41.399
He is not my father.

04:41.424 --> 04:43.609
He's my ex-best friend.

04:44.244 --> 04:46.388
__

04:46.413 --> 04:48.971
Toshi, you finally learned
another language...

04:48.996 --> 04:50.655
and you chose French?

04:50.657 --> 04:53.058
That's the kind of kissing he does.

04:53.060 --> 04:54.922
[LOUDLY KISSES]

04:54.947 --> 04:56.178
Ooh, la, la.

04:56.670 --> 04:58.131
Croissant.

04:59.078 --> 05:00.229
[BAM!]

05:00.254 --> 05:01.729
Hey, everyone.

05:01.754 --> 05:02.794
Papa Toshi.

05:02.819 --> 05:05.400
Whoa, you only had one kid
in your Christmas card.

05:05.425 --> 05:06.759
That was ten years ago.

05:06.784 --> 05:08.157
I wish it were 15.

05:08.182 --> 05:10.209
You must be the little darlings

05:10.211 --> 05:12.560
my daughter's been keeping from me.

05:12.585 --> 05:14.545
As a good mother, I try to shield them

05:14.570 --> 05:16.857
from drunk housewives and bad haircuts.

05:18.151 --> 05:19.774
I hope you wike it.

05:20.694 --> 05:23.847
I puwled the skeweton out awl by mysewf.

05:23.872 --> 05:25.090
JEFF: That's Noah.

05:25.414 --> 05:27.626
[QUIETLY] We're a little
worried about him.

05:27.628 --> 05:29.451
Has trouble saying "L" 's.

05:29.709 --> 05:32.764
[RUMBLING]

05:32.789 --> 05:35.700
What up, sluts? Happy Klaus's funeral.

05:35.702 --> 05:37.969
Roger! My floor!

05:37.971 --> 05:39.170
Cool, right?

05:39.172 --> 05:41.266
Above-ground traffic is for poor people.

05:41.291 --> 05:43.219
I got here from Tokyo in 20 minutes.

05:43.244 --> 05:44.506
Bored right through the core.

05:44.531 --> 05:46.311
No poors in the core, baby.

05:46.313 --> 05:48.972
[METALLIC RATTLING]

05:50.170 --> 05:51.934
Veela, why aren't you stealing anything?

05:51.959 --> 05:55.128
Stan! How the hell did
you get in my house?!

05:55.153 --> 05:59.038
I, uh, still have a key to the backdoor.

06:01.805 --> 06:03.672
Dad, it's good to...

06:05.006 --> 06:06.197
Y-You look...

06:06.199 --> 06:07.266
Alive.

06:07.268 --> 06:08.800
Oh, you noticed?

06:08.802 --> 06:11.316
Sorry I'm late, gang.
I was busy being awesome,

06:11.341 --> 06:14.072
eating really expensive
cookies whenever I want,

06:14.074 --> 06:17.374
swimming in all the oceans,
and not having any parasites.

06:17.399 --> 06:18.944
[SILVERWARE CLATTERS]

06:19.305 --> 06:22.036
Well, I'm sure you'd all like to unpack.

06:22.061 --> 06:24.242
Hayley, you take your old room.

06:24.267 --> 06:26.698
Steve, you share the attic with Roger.

06:26.723 --> 06:30.822
Toshi and I turned your bedroom
into an ass-blast-itorium.

06:30.824 --> 06:32.426
[CHUCKLES DERISIVELY] Real creative.

06:32.451 --> 06:36.448
Hey, don't turn my kitchen
into a sass-back-itorium!

06:36.630 --> 06:38.385
Stan, there's a blanket in the basement.

06:38.410 --> 06:42.229
Sure, I... I guess I could cancel
my suite at the Four Seasons...

06:42.254 --> 06:44.853
<i>and</i> my expensive prostitute.

06:45.300 --> 06:47.750
♪♪

06:47.775 --> 06:48.854
[TYPES ON KEYBOARD]

06:48.879 --> 06:52.273
[RUMBLING]

06:54.585 --> 06:57.031
Can you believe these
little drills are optional?

06:57.056 --> 07:00.519
If I didn't have a little drill,
I'd kill myself like Klaus.

07:00.521 --> 07:02.453
I'm assuming it was a suicide?

07:02.455 --> 07:04.034
Do we know? Do we care?

07:04.059 --> 07:05.059
I don't know.

07:05.084 --> 07:06.883
- The woman who called Douglas...
- Douglas?

07:06.908 --> 07:08.352
- My jerk-off robot...
- Your what?

07:08.377 --> 07:09.524
My regular robot!

07:11.128 --> 07:14.090
The woman who called Douglas
was light on details...

07:14.115 --> 07:15.400
of Klaus's death.

07:15.402 --> 07:17.336
Which is the topic of this conversation.

07:17.338 --> 07:19.461
Master, you seem tense.

07:19.486 --> 07:21.807
Would you like to jerk me off?

07:21.809 --> 07:24.569
Wait. You do him?

07:26.142 --> 07:28.146
[SING-SONGY] Awkward.

07:30.754 --> 07:34.411
♪♪

07:34.436 --> 07:37.298
Thank you all for coming
on such short notice.

07:37.323 --> 07:39.201
I'm Sister Madeline.

07:39.226 --> 07:43.165
I met Klaus while passing out
food and blankets on Skid Row.

07:43.994 --> 07:45.201
Excuse me, Stan Smith.

07:45.226 --> 07:46.832
I'd like to start by
saying I was invited

07:46.834 --> 07:48.296
so I'm allowed to be here.

07:48.321 --> 07:50.849
Now, where are you passing
out these free blankets?

07:51.679 --> 07:55.279
I was with Klaus in his final moments.

07:55.304 --> 07:57.797
He requested that I
gather you all together

07:57.822 --> 08:00.119
and show you this video.

08:01.041 --> 08:03.323
Dearest Smiths... [COUGHS]

08:03.926 --> 08:06.117
... I bet you always
wondered what happened

08:06.119 --> 08:08.112
- to good, ol' Klaus.
- Nope.

08:08.137 --> 08:10.401
- Not me.
- Oh, that Klaus!

08:10.679 --> 08:15.787
Well, [COUGHS] after
I left, my life went downhill.

08:15.812 --> 08:19.204
I caught Hep C from a plum
at the 99 cent store.

08:19.229 --> 08:21.335
And because I didn't have insurance,

08:21.360 --> 08:23.191
I joined the army,

08:23.216 --> 08:25.693
but they sent me directly
to the Moon Wars

08:25.718 --> 08:27.648
where I went completely insane

08:27.673 --> 08:30.742
after my brain was
infested with moon mites.

08:30.744 --> 08:32.082
[COUGHS]

08:32.107 --> 08:35.070
But I never blamed you guys.

08:35.095 --> 08:37.066
You were the only family...

08:38.085 --> 08:40.210
I ever loved.

08:40.631 --> 08:43.054
[COUGHS]

08:46.395 --> 08:47.826
Was that a snuff film?

08:47.828 --> 08:49.761
You should be ashamed of yourselves!

08:49.763 --> 08:52.082
You all turned your back on your friend,

08:52.107 --> 08:54.165
and he died alone.

08:54.167 --> 08:56.143
What do you want us
to do about it, lady?

08:56.168 --> 08:57.779
Give him a proper funeral!

08:57.804 --> 08:59.438
Say some nice things!

08:59.440 --> 09:01.306
Throw in one of those blankets
you've been yapping about

09:01.308 --> 09:03.642
and we got a deal,
but I want it upfront.

09:03.976 --> 09:05.907
I've been burned before.

09:06.179 --> 09:08.123
Fine. We'll throw
Klaus a stupid funeral.

09:08.148 --> 09:10.937
- Then will you feel better?
- This isn't about me.

09:11.843 --> 09:14.058
- It's about Klaus!
- [DOOR SLAMS]

09:14.083 --> 09:16.941
Oh, but it is about me.

09:16.966 --> 09:19.524
[VOICE DEEPENING] And it's about Klaus,

09:19.526 --> 09:23.363
for I... am... Klaus!

09:24.322 --> 09:25.546
Sorry, did you say something?

09:25.571 --> 09:27.799
[HIGH-PITCHED VOICE] Oh,
just conversing with the Lord.

09:27.801 --> 09:29.439
He's the best, you know.

09:30.516 --> 09:31.710
Okay.

09:32.139 --> 09:33.872
Remember the blanket.

09:35.953 --> 09:36.953
[DOOR SLAMS]

09:38.150 --> 09:40.322
♪♪

09:40.347 --> 09:42.347
So everyone has their assignments

09:42.349 --> 09:44.455
for Klaus's funeral preparations.

09:44.480 --> 09:45.884
By the way, where's Jeff?

09:45.886 --> 09:47.196
I sent him home with the kids.

09:47.221 --> 09:48.896
He wasn't here when we had Klaus.

09:48.921 --> 09:51.022
What?! Yes, he was!

09:51.024 --> 09:53.030
I'm... assuming...

09:53.204 --> 09:56.027
based on information
available to anybody.

09:56.029 --> 09:58.065
Come on, let's get this over with.

09:58.098 --> 09:59.898
This isn't something to "get over with."

09:59.900 --> 10:01.099
It's a chance to come to terms

10:01.101 --> 10:03.746
with the great loss you all must feel.

10:04.183 --> 10:05.413
Quick question...

10:05.659 --> 10:06.772
You're Klaus, right?

10:06.774 --> 10:08.449
What?! Who's Klaus?!

10:08.474 --> 10:11.243
That's... not what you'd say.

10:11.245 --> 10:13.644
[NORMAL VOICE] Okay,
this family owes me an apology.

10:13.669 --> 10:16.139
They were wrong to treat me so badly.

10:16.164 --> 10:19.708
And once the sobering reality
of my funeral hits them,

10:19.733 --> 10:21.305
they'll sob,

10:21.330 --> 10:22.831
they'll wail,

10:22.856 --> 10:25.758
they'll beg the heavens for my return!

10:26.237 --> 10:29.750
Huh. So it's a goof. That's pretty cool!

10:29.775 --> 10:32.108
Oh, you know what would be a
good way to reveal you're alive?

10:32.132 --> 10:33.799
When they're kneeling
in front of your casket,

10:33.801 --> 10:35.501
just, like, fart really loud.

10:35.526 --> 10:37.469
[CHUCKLES] No, wait. That's too good.

10:37.471 --> 10:38.498
I want to do that.

10:38.523 --> 10:41.222
Oh, man, I am gonna be
the hit of the funeral!

10:41.247 --> 10:44.057
Us at Familyland. Us at the beach.

10:44.082 --> 10:47.078
Oh, look. Remember
when we ate this pasta?

10:47.080 --> 10:50.375
Oh, my God. Yes! It was so good!

10:50.400 --> 10:51.817
I got full, though.

10:51.819 --> 10:54.419
Hey, I'm sorry we lost touch.

10:54.421 --> 10:56.644
- What happened to us?
- I don't know.

10:56.669 --> 10:58.490
The pictures stop after the pasta.

10:58.492 --> 11:00.556
[HIGH-PITCHED VOICE]
How's it going down here?

11:00.581 --> 11:03.592
Have you found any good photos
of Klaus for the slideshow?

11:03.617 --> 11:05.297
Actually, it doesn't seem
like we have any.

11:05.299 --> 11:07.293
What?! How is that possible?

11:07.318 --> 11:09.096
I guess we didn't have
an underwater camera.

11:09.121 --> 11:12.783
Jesus H., how stupid are you?
He lived in a bowl.

11:12.808 --> 11:15.264
You don't have to put the
camera in the bowl.

11:15.289 --> 11:17.568
Why do you have such a boner for Klaus?

11:17.593 --> 11:18.940
Aren't you married to God?

11:18.965 --> 11:20.365
Just find a picture!

11:22.565 --> 11:24.693
Oh, here's one with
Klaus in the background.

11:24.829 --> 11:26.963
That's a tangerine.

11:29.389 --> 11:31.363
Eh. We'll just draw some eyes on it.

11:31.388 --> 11:34.325
[SCISSORS SNIPPING]

11:35.659 --> 11:37.524
Stan, what are you doing?

11:37.549 --> 11:40.782
Aren't... Aren't they asparagus?
[MUNCHING]

11:43.080 --> 11:45.403
God, how are you even alive?

11:45.405 --> 11:47.767
Francine, I have to come clean with you.

11:48.362 --> 11:51.134
I'm not doing as well as I maybe look.

11:51.159 --> 11:52.678
You look like you're dying.

11:52.680 --> 11:53.945
That's just a facade.

11:53.947 --> 11:55.743
My life's not a fairy tale.

11:56.216 --> 11:57.736
This is a ferret tail.

11:57.761 --> 12:00.850
Nah, things aren't that
great for me either.

12:00.875 --> 12:04.434
I have to confess,
when I agreed to marry Toshi,

12:04.459 --> 12:06.556
I had him confused with Snot.

12:06.581 --> 12:09.734
I feel like everything changed
for us after the divorce.

12:09.759 --> 12:11.395
People don't talk about that part.

12:11.420 --> 12:12.865
What happened to us?

12:12.890 --> 12:15.068
When did everything become a fight?

12:15.733 --> 12:16.733
I'm sorry.

12:16.758 --> 12:18.020
Sorry about Klaus?!

12:18.045 --> 12:20.944
No, we're talking about
our marriage falling apart.

12:20.969 --> 12:22.040
Ever heard of it?

12:22.042 --> 12:23.641
Well, start talking about Klaus

12:23.643 --> 12:26.308
or I'll tell God you
should all go to hell!

12:26.333 --> 12:27.952
Ever heard of that?

12:30.448 --> 12:33.513
[STAMMERS] This robot
was trying to get fresh.

12:33.538 --> 12:35.865
[NORMALLY] Can you believe this family?

12:35.890 --> 12:38.056
All they care about is themselves.

12:38.058 --> 12:39.949
Wow, you sound like Klaus!

12:39.993 --> 12:41.327
[STAMMERS] I am Klaus!

12:41.329 --> 12:43.245
Oh, yeah. Oh, oh, you got that plan.

12:43.277 --> 12:44.898
You're going to fart or
something at a funeral?

12:44.922 --> 12:45.997
Ugh. That's so stupid.

12:45.999 --> 12:47.265
That was your idea!

12:47.267 --> 12:49.505
Well, I see how it could work.

12:49.530 --> 12:51.635
I guess it would all
depend on the execution.

12:51.939 --> 12:53.193
Well, good luck at the wedding.

12:55.713 --> 12:59.548
♪♪

13:00.494 --> 13:01.747
[SLOWLY] ♪ Hey, now ♪

13:01.749 --> 13:03.163
♪ You're an all-star ♪

13:03.188 --> 13:04.750
♪ Get your game on ♪

13:04.752 --> 13:06.818
♪ Go, play ♪

13:06.820 --> 13:08.153
♪ Hey now ♪

13:08.155 --> 13:09.567
♪ You're a rock star ♪

13:09.592 --> 13:10.956
♪ Get the show on ♪

13:10.958 --> 13:12.570
♪ Get paid ♪

13:12.595 --> 13:16.527
♪ And all that glitters is gold ♪

13:16.552 --> 13:22.103
♪ Only shooting stars break the mold ♪

13:25.316 --> 13:27.973
[HIGH-PITCHED VOICE]
Klaus was a special fish

13:27.975 --> 13:31.002
who swam his way into our hearts.

13:31.027 --> 13:34.380
Perhaps someone would
like to say a few words?

13:34.382 --> 13:35.581
Stan?

13:38.396 --> 13:39.729
Uh, okay.

13:39.754 --> 13:41.117
Uh, Klaus.

13:41.601 --> 13:43.589
Well, he was a fish. We know that.

13:44.136 --> 13:46.481
And he lived in our
house for a few weeks.

13:46.506 --> 13:47.905
For years!

13:48.957 --> 13:51.196
Maybe focus on your emotions.

13:51.198 --> 13:54.606
Like crippling guilt
or haunting remorse?

13:56.244 --> 13:57.840
[CRIES]

13:57.865 --> 14:00.583
Yes, it's okay to cry.

14:00.608 --> 14:02.718
Let it flow.

14:02.743 --> 14:05.307
[LAUGHING] I'm sorry.
I'm not crying, I'm laughing.

14:05.332 --> 14:07.613
I'm just remembering this time
Klaus tried to convince us

14:07.615 --> 14:10.015
he could kick a football
over a Burger King.

14:10.017 --> 14:12.450
Ha! He was such a liar.

14:12.475 --> 14:13.751
Remember when he told us

14:13.753 --> 14:16.554
he beat up Brett Favre
at a mini-golf course?

14:16.556 --> 14:19.110
- FRANCINE: What an idiot!
- [LAUGHTER]

14:19.135 --> 14:20.358
Check this out, guys.

14:20.360 --> 14:22.758
I always said Klaus was a wiener.

14:23.417 --> 14:27.075
[NORMALLY] Shut up! Shut up!

14:27.100 --> 14:28.975
You guys are ruining my funeral!

14:29.000 --> 14:31.099
Whoa, you do a better Klaus than he did.

14:31.124 --> 14:32.391
I am Klaus!

14:32.416 --> 14:34.205
Klaus, now's the time for the fart.

14:34.230 --> 14:35.331
Shut up.

14:35.356 --> 14:39.724
I gave you all every chance to
say one decent thing about me.

14:39.749 --> 14:43.412
And now, I'll give you one final chance.

14:44.318 --> 14:45.883
Did you kill a nun?

14:45.908 --> 14:46.995
That's it!

14:48.140 --> 14:51.235
Whoa, this is gonna be some fart.

14:51.260 --> 14:53.492
[CAN HISSING]

14:53.517 --> 14:55.294
Wowee.

14:55.319 --> 14:56.652
[MULTIPLE THUDS]

14:58.873 --> 15:01.112
STEVE: What... What's going on?

15:01.137 --> 15:02.972
FRANCINE: Where are we?

15:08.676 --> 15:10.942
We're... underwater.

15:10.944 --> 15:13.078
And we're in the attic.

15:13.103 --> 15:15.747
Oh, crap. We're in Klaus's bowl.

15:15.749 --> 15:17.685
No, it's worse.

15:17.710 --> 15:19.301
We're in Klaus's body.

15:19.326 --> 15:21.945
Bingo, jerkwads.

15:23.134 --> 15:25.000
Welcome to hell,

15:25.025 --> 15:27.418
otherwise known as my life.

15:27.443 --> 15:29.062
Oh, my God.

15:29.087 --> 15:30.762
I left my charger out there

15:30.764 --> 15:32.364
and my phone's at 4%!

15:32.366 --> 15:34.371
This is gonna suck!

15:35.929 --> 15:38.347
♪♪

15:38.372 --> 15:40.372
STEVE: Klaus, what the hell is going on?

15:40.397 --> 15:43.562
You shrunk us down and put
us in a fish-sized submarine?

15:43.587 --> 15:45.191
Don't be stupid, Steve.

15:45.216 --> 15:46.938
Even science has its limits.

15:46.963 --> 15:50.149
I simply transferred all of your
consciousnesses into my body,

15:50.174 --> 15:52.460
so you'd feel what it's like to be me.

15:52.485 --> 15:53.656
No more questions!

15:53.681 --> 15:56.068
Wait, why did you put yourself in here?

15:56.093 --> 15:57.322
Great question.

15:57.578 --> 15:58.705
That was a mistake.

15:59.326 --> 16:00.802
Okay, quick poll.

16:00.827 --> 16:03.241
Who wants to learn Klaus's dumb lesson?

16:03.266 --> 16:05.149
Not me. I want to watch TV.

16:05.174 --> 16:08.299
We've got to find someone
to help us get back into our bodies.

16:08.324 --> 16:11.589
Maybe we can use these
controls to call for help.

16:11.614 --> 16:13.248
Blat! Eep! Ooh!

16:13.273 --> 16:14.339
You don't know what you're doing.

16:14.341 --> 16:15.557
Use one of the presets.

16:15.807 --> 16:17.645
Wuzzuuuuuuuup!

16:18.305 --> 16:19.861
[IMITATING BORAT] My wife!

16:20.635 --> 16:22.902
[NORMALLY] It's five to
watch, ten to touch.

16:23.750 --> 16:25.716
I... I used to work at a movie theater

16:25.741 --> 16:27.820
where it cost extra to touch the screen.

16:27.822 --> 16:30.268
Eh, you clowns, get out of the way.

16:30.491 --> 16:33.291
There's his cup.
That's how he gets around.

16:34.259 --> 16:36.005
- [CONSOLE BEEPS]
- [WATER SLOSHES]

16:36.030 --> 16:37.466
Nice move, Francine.

16:37.491 --> 16:39.191
It's obviously the levers.

16:41.435 --> 16:44.536
Yeah! Daddy just dunked on y'all!

16:46.613 --> 16:47.710
Stan!

16:47.735 --> 16:51.020
♪♪

16:51.045 --> 16:52.720
Who lit a Yankee candle?

16:52.745 --> 16:54.312
I like the smell of cookies,

16:54.314 --> 16:56.160
but I don't have the time to bake.

16:56.185 --> 16:58.908
Klaus, you've got to help us.
We're all gonna die.

16:58.933 --> 17:01.319
[SCOFFS] I don't care if I die.

17:01.321 --> 17:04.299
In fact, welcome to my suicide.

17:04.324 --> 17:06.878
[LAUGHS MANIACALLY]

17:06.904 --> 17:07.992
[CONSOLE BEEPING]

17:07.993 --> 17:10.525
[VOCALIZING]

17:10.550 --> 17:15.895
♪♪

17:15.920 --> 17:17.202
STAN: That was lucky.

17:17.204 --> 17:19.550
Now we just have to make
it to the front door.

17:20.853 --> 17:22.721
[GRUNTING]

17:22.746 --> 17:27.136
♪♪

17:27.161 --> 17:28.394
Oh, thank God.

17:28.419 --> 17:30.348
Jeff forgot one of our kids again.

17:31.867 --> 17:33.429
It's... Noah.

17:33.454 --> 17:36.852
[LISPING] Fishy,
your skeleton needs to come out.

17:38.154 --> 17:40.269
The little creep's gonna taxidermy us.

17:40.294 --> 17:42.271
- Go for his knees.
- No, dummy. Choke him.

17:42.296 --> 17:44.240
You idiots, kick him in the balls.

17:44.265 --> 17:46.615
We should be kicking Klaus in the balls.

17:46.640 --> 17:49.158
You can't kick Klaus in
something he doesn't have.

17:49.183 --> 17:50.812
[LAUGHTER]

17:50.837 --> 17:52.215
Good burn, son.

17:52.240 --> 17:53.306
Hayley, you got one?

17:53.331 --> 17:54.950
There's a peanut on the floor.

17:54.975 --> 17:56.641
Hmm, kind of a thinker.

17:56.666 --> 17:58.945
I obviously get it,
but what about the broader audience

17:58.970 --> 18:00.297
you want to reach with your comedy?

18:00.321 --> 18:02.562
No, there's a peanut on the floor.

18:02.587 --> 18:03.719
Noah's allergic.

18:03.744 --> 18:05.913
If you have to explain it,
Hayley, it's not funny.

18:05.938 --> 18:09.187
No, we flick the peanut in Noah's mouth!

18:09.189 --> 18:14.126
♪♪

18:14.128 --> 18:15.128
Fish...

18:15.153 --> 18:17.623
[GAGS]

18:17.648 --> 18:20.205
[COUGHS] I got to get my EpiPen!

18:21.302 --> 18:22.302
ALL: Yes!

18:22.327 --> 18:25.403
Wait. Do you guys
realize what's happening?

18:25.405 --> 18:27.904
When we all make fun of Klaus,

18:27.929 --> 18:30.414
we get along, like at his funeral!

18:30.439 --> 18:34.608
That must be why everything
fell apart after he left.

18:34.633 --> 18:37.938
Klaus is the glue that
holds this family together!

18:37.963 --> 18:40.368
Klaus is incredibly important...

18:40.393 --> 18:42.627
because he sucks so much.

18:43.389 --> 18:44.934
- [GENTLE MUSIC PLAYS]
- Thank you.

18:44.959 --> 18:46.691
That's all I wanted.

18:46.693 --> 18:50.437
I just needed to be
appreciated for something.

18:50.641 --> 18:52.634
- [PICTURE CLATTERS]
- Great, great.

18:52.659 --> 18:54.432
We all love each other again.
Now down the stairs.

18:54.434 --> 19:01.434
♪♪

19:03.682 --> 19:05.745
Klaus, where's your door claw?!

19:05.770 --> 19:07.120
I buried it.

19:07.145 --> 19:08.425
It's what I bludgeoned the nun with

19:08.449 --> 19:10.407
before I stole her body.

19:10.432 --> 19:12.870
Steve, tell your robot to open the door.

19:12.895 --> 19:14.853
I can't. See his eyes?

19:15.484 --> 19:18.378
It's been over 24 hours
since I serviced him.

19:18.403 --> 19:20.004
- What?
- [SIGHS]

19:20.029 --> 19:22.729
Okay, it's not a regular robot.
It's a pleasure bot.

19:22.754 --> 19:25.197
And there's only one way to
get him out of attack mode...

19:25.199 --> 19:26.743
Pleasure him.

19:26.768 --> 19:28.167
Oh, God.

19:28.192 --> 19:29.221
Don't worry.

19:29.246 --> 19:31.269
Together, we can do this.

19:31.271 --> 19:33.568
To battle stations!

19:33.593 --> 19:38.359
♪♪

19:38.384 --> 19:39.850
Follow my lead!

19:39.875 --> 19:41.243
I know what he likes.

19:41.268 --> 19:43.001
[CONSOLES BEEPING]

19:43.026 --> 19:50.026
♪♪

19:52.493 --> 19:55.075
[MECHANICAL MOANING]

19:55.100 --> 19:59.275
[SIGHS HAPPILY]

20:01.479 --> 20:04.013
♪♪

20:04.038 --> 20:05.339
HAYLEY: We made it.

20:05.364 --> 20:07.039
Well, let me take the helm,

20:07.041 --> 20:09.641
and we'll get you back in your bodies.

20:09.643 --> 20:11.643
I want to go find Toshi first.

20:11.645 --> 20:14.446
After all this,
you still want to be with him?

20:14.448 --> 20:16.581
No, I just think it will be easier

20:16.583 --> 20:18.650
to break up with him inside the fish.

20:18.652 --> 20:19.752
You mean it, honey?

20:19.777 --> 20:21.096
Come here you.

20:21.121 --> 20:25.254
♪♪

20:25.279 --> 20:27.808
_

20:27.833 --> 20:31.327
Well, my company was surprised
I moved it to Langley Falls,

20:31.352 --> 20:34.199
but I had to oversee a
very important merger.

20:34.201 --> 20:36.571
To Mom and Dad's second marriage!

20:37.079 --> 20:38.159
[GLASSES CLINK]

20:38.937 --> 20:42.807
Ahem. Guys, it's great to
be back with the family,

20:42.809 --> 20:44.609
and I'd like to say...

20:44.881 --> 20:47.588
[CHANTING] Disposal. Disposal.

20:47.613 --> 20:51.149
ALL: [CHANTING] Disposal!
Disposal! Disposal!

20:51.151 --> 20:52.398
Disposal!

20:54.243 --> 20:57.031
I'm the glue, baby!

20:57.056 --> 20:58.200
[DISPOSAL WHIRRING]

20:58.225 --> 20:59.820
Bye bye! See you soon!

